div.p:
I ſuppoſe it was intended for a Gate or Entrance into the City;
for it fronts the great Street of the Suburbs, and has a vaſt Walk planted
with Trees leading from it towards Bois de Vincennes.

Of Forc't Muſhroomes they have many Crops in a year;
but for the Months of Auguſt, September, October, when they
naturally grow in the Fields, they prepare no Artificial Beds.

Here were very many Fig-Trees well grown in ſquare
Boxes; and Parterrs well ſtockt with Flowers; each ſort by themſelves;
as Tulips a-part; Junkills a-part; Anemonies a-part;
Ranunculus's a-part; Daffadills a-part.
